3. Usage 1. Open the App When the app starts, it may ask you for an APK file or you can select a file from within. The file of your choice will be displayed on the screen.
2. Start Analysis Press the “RUN” analysis button. The program starts analyzing the APK file. 3. Wait The progress bar on the screen shows the analysis process. This may take a few seconds. 4. Review Results After the analysis is complete, you will receive the following information: (1). Package Name of the Application (2). Android Version Support (3). Is the APK Encrypted? (4). Permissions Used (5). Certificate Information (Who signed it?) (6). Algorithm Comments:
CLEAN: Trusted company (Google, Meta, etc.) certificate detected. UNWANTED: Suspicious certificate + risky permissions. MALICIOUS: RAT or dangerous behavior found.
5. Warnings and Warning Icons If a known malware (RAT) is found in the APK, a red Android icon and warning text will appear on the screen. You may see messages like "This APK contains a known RAT signature: ..." or similar messages.
6. When Should I Worry? Be careful in the following situations: The app asks for a lot of special permissions (camera, microphone, message reading, etc.) If the certificate it is signed with has phrases like “Android”, ‘test’, “unknown” and meaningless words and belongs to unrecognized developers and has been labeled “MALICIOUS” or “UNWANTED”.
7. Extra Info APKdevastate automatically deletes temporary files at the end of the analysis. this way there are no unnecessary files on your computer.
8. Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) (1). How long does the analysis take? Depending on the speed of the device and the content of the apk file, it may take between 10-120 seconds. (2). Do I need internet? No, the analysis takes place entirely on your computer. It does not connect to the internet. (3). Does it detect every malicious application? It detects common RATs and suspicious behavior. however, it does not provide a 100% guarantee. It still provides a strong preliminary analysis.
9.Conclusion APKdevastate offers you an easy and effective way to find out if an APK file is safe or not, even if you have no technical knowledge. analyze suspicious apps with this program and protect your device!
I reward you for reading this far, if you click on the android logo on the main screen, the music will play.

data.value: 2. Before You Begin For the application to work correctly: Java must be installed on your computer. APKdevastate folder must contain two special folders named resources and temp (the program creates them automatically). The .apk file you want to analyze must be ready.

data.value: 1. What is APKdevastate? APKdevastate analyzes Android application files (APK) to check for malware (e.g. RAT), suspicious permissions or suspicious certificates. you can use it in a simple way without any technical knowledge.
